.SH NAME
Types::Standard::Dict \- exporter utility and utility functions for the Dict type constraint
.SH STATUS
.IX Header "STATUS"
This module is not covered by the
Type\-Tiny stability policy.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This is mostly internal code, but has one public\-facing function.
.SS Function
.IX Subsection "Function"
.ie n .IP Types::Standard::Dict::combine(@dicts) 4
.el .IP \f(CWTypes::Standard::Dict::combine(@dicts)\fR 4
.IX Item "Types::Standard::Dict::combine(@dicts)"
Creates a combined type constraint, attempting to be permissive.
.Sp
The following two types should be equivalent:
.Sp
.Vb 5
\&  my $type1 = Types::Standard::Dict::combine(
\&    Dict[ name => Str ],
\&    Dict[ age => Int, Slurpy[HashRef[Int]] ],
\&    Dict[ id => Str, name => ArrayRef, Slurpy[ArrayRef] ],
\&  );
\&  
\&  my $type2 = Dict[
\&    name => Str|ArrayRef,
\&    age => Int,
\&    id => Str,
\&    Slurpy[ HashRef[Int] | ArrayRef ],
\&  ];
.Ve
.Sp
Note that a hashref satisfying the combined type wouldn\*(Aqt satisfy any of
the individual \fBDict\fR constraints, nor vice versa!
.Sp
This function can be exported:
.Sp
.Vb 2
\&  use Types::Standard \-types;
\&  use Types::Standard::Dict combine => { \-as => \*(Aqcombine_dicts\*(Aq };
\&  
\&  my $type1 = combine_dicts(
\&    Dict[ name => Str ],
\&    Dict[ age => Int, Slurpy[HashRef[Int]] ],
\&    Dict[ id => Str, name => ArrayRef, Slurpy[ArrayRef] ],
\&  );
.Ve
.SS Exports
.IX Subsection "Exports"
Types::Standard::Dict can be used experimentally as an exporter.
.PP
.Vb 5
\&  use Types::Standard \*(AqStr\*(Aq;
\&  use Types::Standard::Dict Credentials => { of => [
\&    username => Str,
\&    password => Str,
\&  ] };
.Ve
.PP
This will export the following functions into your namespace:
.ie n .IP """Credentials""" 4
.el .IP \f(CWCredentials\fR 4
.IX Item "Credentials"
.PD 0
.ie n .IP "is_Credentials( $value )" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWis_Credentials( $value )\fR" 4
.IX Item "is_Credentials( $value )"
.ie n .IP "assert_Credentials( $value )" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWassert_Credentials( $value )\fR" 4
.IX Item "assert_Credentials( $value )"
.ie n .IP "to_Credentials( $value )" 4
.el .IP "\f(CWto_Credentials( $value )\fR" 4
.IX Item "to_Credentials( $value )"
.PD
.PP
Multiple types can be exported at once:
.PP
.Vb 1
\&  use Types::Standard \-types;
\&  
\&  use Types::Standard::Dict (
\&    Credentials => { of => [
\&      username => Str,
\&      password => Str,
\&    ] },
\&    Headers => { of => [
\&      \*(AqContent\-Type\*(Aq => Optional[Str],
\&      \*(AqAccept\*(Aq       => Optional[Str],
\&      \*(AqUser\-Agent\*(Aq   => Optional[Str],
\&    ] },
\&  );
\&  
\&  # Exporting this separately so it can use the types defined by
\&  # the first export.
\&  use Types::Standard::Dict (
\&    HttpRequestData => { of => [
\&      credentials => Credentials,
\&      headers     => Headers,
\&      url         => Str,
\&      method      => Enum[ qw( OPTIONS HEAD GET POST PUT DELETE PATCH ) ],
\&    ] },
\&  );
\&  
\&  assert_HttpRequestData( {
\&    credentials => { username => \*(Aqbob\*(Aq, password => \*(Aqs3cr3t\*(Aq },
\&    headers     => { \*(AqAccept\*(Aq => \*(Aqapplication/json\*(Aq },
\&    url         => \*(Aqhttp://example.net/api/v1/stuff\*(Aq,
\&    method      => \*(AqGET\*(Aq,
\&  } );
.Ve
.PP
It\*(Aqs possible to further constrain the hashref using \f(CW\*(C`where\*(C'\fR:
.PP
.Vb 1
\&  use Types::Standard::Dict MyThing => { of => [ ... ], where => sub { ... } };
.Ve
